HEADWORD: Spermatin
<hw>Sper"ma*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance allied to alkali albumin and to mucin,
present in semen, to which it is said to impart the mucilaginous
character.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spermatism</ent>⟦br⟧
